 Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Lavagna","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carmine, Attilio, Carlo, Cataldo, Enrico, Gaetano, Gennaro, Rocco, Sal.  Spanish Alfonso, Glicerio, Liborio.","Italian: ethnic name for a member of the Alemanni, an ancient Germanic people inhabiting what is now southern Germany, from a shortened form of <b>Alamagna</b> ‘Alemannia’, i.e. ‘land of the Alemanni’. Compare   Lamanna  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lamanna","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Rocco, Carlo, Carmine, Vito, Luigi, Pasquale, Sal, Amedeo, Anella, Angelo, Carmelo.","Italian (southern):","(also <b>La Manna</b>): topographic name from <i>manna</i>, a term denoting a type of ash tree, + the definite article <i>la</i>."]}]},{"name":"Eleonora","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Eleanor  , now sometimes also used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleonora Fieschi di Lavagna was born in 1265, in Lavagna, Genova, Liguria, Italy, her father, Frédéric Fieschi, was 35 and her mother, Chiara Volta, was 35. She had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Bernabò DORIA. She died in 1333, in Savona, Liguria, Italy, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1265–1333":"1265–1333","–Female":"Surnud","1260–1336":"1260–1336","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1286–Male":"1286–Surnud","1290–1359":"1290–1359","1290–1367":"1290–1367","1230–1303":"1230–1303","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","about 1280":"umbes 1280","6 février 1303":"6. veebruar 1303","1286":"1286","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1359":"1359","1303":"1303","1336":"1336","1367":"1367","1333":"1333","1265":"1265","Genova, Liguria, Italy":"Genova, Liguria, Itaalia","Sarzana, Province of La Spezia, Liguna,m Italy":"Sarzana, La Spezia, Liguria, Itaalia","Italy":"Itaalia","Rome, Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roma, Roma, Lazio, Itaalia","Savona, Liguria, Italie":"Savona, Liguria, Itaalia","Lavagna, Genova, Liguria, Italie":"Lavagna, Genova, Liguria, Itaalia","Genova, Provincia di Genova, Liguria, Italy":"Genova, Genova, Liguria, Itaalia"},"fi":{"1265–1333":"1265–1333","–Female":"Kuollut","1260–1336":"1260–1336","1280–Female":"1280–Kuollut","1286–Male":"1286–Kuollut","1290–1359":"1290–1359","1290–1367":"1290–1367","1230–1303":"1230–1303","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","about 1280":"noin 1280","6 février 1303":"6. helmikuuta 1303","1286":"1286","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","1